---
layout: base.njk
title: Capydocs Plugins & Themes
description: List of plugins and themes to use along Capydocs.
---
<style>
  .overview {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #cdd0d6;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .collection {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section-kicker {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: #6ce4ff;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    max-width: 640px;
    color: #b5b9c3;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .section-count {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #b5b9c3;
  }

  .plugin-grid,
  .theme-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  }

  .plugin-card,
  .theme-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    background: rgba(21, 23, 31, 0.85);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .plugin-eyebrow,
  .theme-eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #ffb4c8;
  }

  .plugin-card h2,
  .theme-card h2 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .plugin-meta,
  .theme-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #b5b9c3;
  }

  .plugin-meta span,
  .theme-meta span {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.8rem;
  }

  .plugin-links,
  .theme-links {
    margin-top: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .plugin-links a,
  .theme-links a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }
</style>

<section class="overview">
  <p>
    Each folder inside <code>/plugins</code> ships a <code>plugin.json</code> manifest plus an iframe entry file. Eleventy
    exposes those manifests, the raw assets, and <code><a href="/plugins.json">/plugins.json</a></code> so Capydocs can
    auto-install custom handlers.
  </p>
  <p>
    Each folder inside <code>/themes</code> ships a <code>theme.json</code> manifest that Capydocs ingests to register a
    custom theme. The catalog below mirrors every folder and powers <code><a href="/themes.json">/themes.json</a></code>
    for CI/CD pipelines.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="collection">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">Plugins</p>
      <h2>Custom extension handlers</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Bundle these folders under <code>/plugins</code> and Capydocs will load the entry iframe.
      </p>
    </div>
    <span class="section-count">{{ plugins | length }} available</span>
  </div>
  <div class="plugin-grid">
    {% for plugin in plugins %}
      <article class="plugin-card">
        <span class="plugin-eyebrow">Plugin</span>
        <h2>{{ plugin.name }}</h2>
        <p>{{ plugin.description or "No description" }}</p>
        <div class="plugin-meta">
          <span>ID: <code>{{ plugin.id }}</code></span>
          <span>Entry: <code>{{ plugin.entry }}</code></span>
          <span>Sandbox: <code>{{ plugin.sandbox or "default" }}</code></span>
        </div>
        <div class="plugin-links">
          <a href="{{ plugin.entryUrl }}">Entry</a>
          <a href="{{ plugin.manifestUrl }}">Manifest</a>
          <a href="{{ plugin.zipUrl }}" download>ZIP</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="collection">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">Themes</p>
      <h2>Visual styles</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Each theme folder ships a manifest, CSS entrypoint, and any supporting assets. Drop them under
        <code>/themes</code> inside your deployment target.
      </p>
    </div>
    <span class="section-count">{{ themes | length }} available</span>
  </div>
  <div class="theme-grid">
  {% for theme in themes %}
    <article class="theme-card">
      <span class="theme-eyebrow">{{ theme.base | upper }} base</span>
      <h2>{{ theme.name }}</h2>
      <p>{{ theme.description or "No description" }}</p>
      <div class="theme-meta">
        <span>ID: <code>{{ theme.id }}</code></span>
        <span>Version: <code>{{ theme.version }}</code></span>
        <span>Assets: <code>{{ theme.assetsUrl }}</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="theme-links">
        <a href="{{ theme.cssUrl }}">CSS</a>
        <a href="{{ theme.assetsUrl }}/theme.json">Manifest</a>
        <a href="{{ theme.zipUrl }}" download>ZIP</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
</section>
